  "texts": [
    "The prompt included the range of stressful life events from the Holmes and Rahe scale [35].",
    "This scale is one of the most widely used scales for assessing stressful life events [6]; however, it lacks specific events important for historically marginalized groups.",
    "To mitigate this issue, we added some examples of these events identified during our recent scoping review [4].",
    "The LLM had to extract stressful life event and one of the three temporal aspects of the event: (1) the year when the event happened, or (2) An indication that it happened recently, or (3) An indication that the year or recency of the event could not be determined.",
    "We included a few stressful events deemed positive (or at least positive for most people), such as getting married or starting to date."
  ],
